MBOMBELA – Johan Louwrens (23), who faces charges of culpable homicide after a hitand-run which claimed the life of local businesswoman, Letisia Niemann (38) almost two weeks ago, appeared in Court B at the Nelspruit District Court on Wednesday for his bail application. Letisia Niemann sustained fatal injuries in the accident. ALSO READ: Pediatric Care Africa provides life-changing surgery for young Mozambican teen

The Steelpoort resident was granted bail of R1 500 and is due back in court on November 29.